    "body": "There's something strange here.  For me, it works on Ubuntu 16.04, but not on Centos 7.  \r\n\r\nIn particular, after ```make install``` the soft-link _/usr/local/lib/libgrpc++.so.1_ exists on Ubuntu, but not on Centos.\r\n\r\nHere's some Dockerfiles....\r\n\r\nThe following works ok:\r\n```\r\nFROM ubuntu:16.04\r\n\r\n# Update environment and install dependencies\r\nRUN apt-get update && \\\r\n    apt-get -y install \\\r\n  \tbuild-essential \\\r\n\tautoconf \\\r\n\tlibtool \\\r\n\tlibgflags-dev \\\r\n\tlibgtest-dev \\\r\n\tclang \\\r\n\tlibc++-dev \\\r\n\tcurl \\\r\n\tgit && \\\r\n    apt-get clean\r\n\r\n# Clone latest GRPC, build and install  \r\nRUN cd /usr/local/src && \\\r\n    git clone -b v1.4.2 https://github.com/grpc/grpc && \\\r\n    cd grpc && \\\r\n    git submodule update --init && \\\r\n    make -j 8 && \\\r\n    make install\r\n\r\n# Create a simple test application that links against grpc++ and does not crash at runtime\r\nRUN cd /usr/local/src && \\\r\n    mkdir test-app && \\\r\n    echo \"int main() {}\" > main.cpp && \\\r\n    g++ -L/usr/local/lib -lgrpc++ main.cpp -o main && \\\r\n    ./main\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe following fails:\r\n```\r\nFROM centos:7\r\n\r\n# Update environment and install dependencies\r\nRUN yum update -y && \\\r\n    yum install -y \\\r\n  \tbuild-essential \\\r\n\tautoconf \\\r\n\tlibtool \\\r\n\tgflags-develop \\\r\n\tgtest-develop \\\r\n\tclang \\\r\n\tlibstdc++-devel \\\r\n\tcurl \\\r\n\tgit \\\r\n\tmake \\ \r\n\tgcc \\\r\n\tgcc-c++ \\\r\n\twhich && \\\r\n    yum clean all\r\n  \r\n# Clone latest GRPC, build and install  \r\nRUN cd /usr/local/src && \\\r\n    git clone -b v1.4.2 https://github.com/grpc/grpc && \\\r\n    cd grpc && \\\r\n    git submodule update --init && \\\r\n    make -j 8 && \\\r\n    make install\r\n\r\n# Create a simple test application that links against grpc++ and crashes at runtime\r\nRUN cd /usr/local/src && \\\r\n    mkdir test-app && \\\r\n    echo \"int main() {}\" > main.cpp && \\\r\n    g++ -L/usr/local/lib -lgrpc++ main.cpp -o main && \\\r\n    ./main\r\n\r\n```"
